# unplugin-icons Import Convention

This project uses `unplugin-icons` with the Next.js webpack plugin. Icon imports must include a `.jsx` extension so Next resolves them as compiled React components instead of filesystem paths.

Required dev dependencies: `unplugin-icons`, `@svgr/core`, `@svgr/plugin-jsx`, and the relevant `@iconify-json/*` packs.

## Required

```typescript
import AccountIcon from '~icons/mdi/account.jsx';
import GiftIcon from '~icons/solar/gift-bold.jsx';
```

## Forbidden

```typescript
import AccountIcon from '~icons/mdi/account';
import GiftIcon from '~icons/mdi/gift-outline.tsx';
```

## Rules

- Always use the `~icons/<set>/<icon-name>.jsx` import path.
- Always end the import with `.jsx` — never omit the extension or use `.ts`/`.tsx`.
- Import icons as default exports and render them as components: `<AccountIcon />`.
- Place icon imports in a dedicated `// Icons` block, matching existing project style.
